        <p>The one exception to this is in the progression <chord root="I"/><ndash/><chord root="V" bps="4 3"/><ndash/><chord root="I" bps="6"/>, which closes the theme of the first movement of Mozartâ€™s Piano Sonata K. 331.</p>
        <figure>
            <caption>Mozart, Piano Sonata K. 331, I</caption>
            <idx><h>Mozart, W.A.</h><h>Piano Sonata K. 331, I</h></idx>
